---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'October 10, 2025';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy | WebnDigital"
  description="Learn about how WebnDigital uses cookies and similar technologies to enhance your browsing experience."
  keywords="cookie policy, cookies, tracking, website analytics"
  noIndex={true}
>
  <section class="legal-page section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last Updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

        <div class="legal-intro">
          <p>
            This Cookie Policy explains how WebnDigital uses cookies and similar technologies when you visit our website. We use cookies to improve your browsing experience and understand how you interact with our site.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device (computer, tablet, or mobile) when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and provide information to website owners.
        </p>
        <p>
          Cookies help us recognize you, remember your preferences, and improve your overall experience on our website.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
        
        <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They enable basic functions like page navigation and access to secure areas of the website. The website cannot function properly without these cookies.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Session cookies for maintaining your browsing session</li>
          <li>Security cookies for authentication</li>
          <li>Cookie consent preferences</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting and reporting information anonymously. This helps us improve our website's functionality and content.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Google Analytics (anonymized)</li>
          <li>Page view tracking</li>
          <li>User journey analysis</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Functionality Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These cookies allow the website to remember choices you make (such as your language preference) and provide enhanced, more personal features.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Language preferences</li>
          <li>Region selection</li>
          <li>Personalized content</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          We may use third-party service providers who set cookies on our website to help us analyze website usage and improve our services. These third parties include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> For website analytics and performance monitoring</li>
          <li><strong>Vercel Analytics:</strong> For website performance and visitor statistics</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These third parties have their own privacy policies and cookie policies, which we encourage you to review.
        </p>

        <h2>4. How Long Do Cookies Last?</h2>
        
        <h3>Session Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These are temporary cookies that expire when you close your browser. They help the website remember your actions during a single browsing session.
        </p>

        <h3>Persistent Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These cookies remain on your device for a set period or until you delete them. They help us recognize you when you return to our website and remember your preferences.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our cookie consent preference is stored for 365 days.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Managing Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to decide whether to accept or reject cookies. You can manage your cookie preferences through:
        </p>

        <h3>Cookie Consent Banner</h3>
        <p>
          When you first visit our website, you'll see a cookie consent banner. You can choose to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Accept All:</strong> Allow all cookies for the best experience</li>
          <li><strong>Reject All:</strong> Only essential cookies will be used</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Browser Settings</h3>
        <p>
          Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Block all cookies</li>
          <li>Block third-party cookies</li>
          <li>Delete cookies after you close your browser</li>
          <li>Delete specific cookies</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Please note that blocking or deleting cookies may impact your ability to use certain features of our website.
        </p>

        <h3>Browser-Specific Instructions</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data</li>
          <li><strong>Mozilla Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
          <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
          <li><strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions → Cookies and site data</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Do Not Track Signals</h2>
        <p>
          Some browsers include a "Do Not Track" (DNT) feature that signals to websites that you do not want your online activity tracked. We respect DNT signals and will not track users who have DNT enabled.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Cookies and Personal Data</h2>
        <p>
          Some cookies may collect personal data. Any personal data collected through cookies is handled in accordance with our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>. We ensure that:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Data collected is used only for specified purposes</li>
          <li>Data is stored securely</li>
          <li>Data is not shared with third parties without consent</li>
          <li>You can request deletion of your data at any time</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Updates to This Cookie Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
        </p>
        <p>
          The "Last Updated" date at the top of this page indicates when this policy was last revised.
        </p>

        <h2>9. More Information</h2>
        <p>
          For more information about cookies and how to manage them, you can visit:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.allaboutcookies.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">All About Cookies</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Your Online Choices</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/online/cookies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">UK ICO Cookie Guidance</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about our use of cookies, please contact us:</p>
        <div class="contact-info-box">
          <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@webndigital.co.uk">hello@webndigital.co.uk</a></p>
          <p><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+447902844675">+44 7902 844675</a></p>
          <p><strong>Address:</strong> London, United Kingdom</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .legal-intro {
    background: #F8FAFC;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
  }

  .legal-intro p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-gray);
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-gray);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-gray);
  }

  .legal-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--transition-base);
  }

  .legal-content a:hover {
    color: #007AD9;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .contact-info-box {
    background: #F8FAFC;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .contact-info-box p {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-page {
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .legal-content {
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }

    .legal-content h1 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    .legal-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>

